Sec. 93.053. FEES. A public weigher is entitled to receive a
fee in the following amount as full payment for issuance of a weight
certificate:
(1) 10 cents if a net load weighs, 7,000 pounds or less;
(2) 15 cents if a net load weighs more than 7,000 pounds
but not more than 14,000 pounds; or
(3) 20 cents if a net load weighs more than 14,000 pounds.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1240, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

